Summary:<ul> <li>AGOA trade initiative expires in 2025翻译:AGOA 贸易倡议将于 2025 年到期</li>  <li>Africans want early renewal, with possible changes after翻译:非洲人希望尽早更新，之后可能会发生变化</li>  <li>U.S. administration says AGOA needs updating翻译:美国政府表示 AGOA 需要更新</li> </ul>      <figure><img src="https://www.reuters.com/resizer/EE7ua3WKUmiTdfFne93UgGbTJ7k=/1920x0/filters:quality(80)/cloudfront-us-east-2.images.arcpublishing.com/reuters/3XQO5RV2PVMONDCXKX3VED6E7M.jpg" alt="U.S. Secretary of State Blinken departs on trip to the Middle East and Asia from Joint Base Andrews in Maryland" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"><figcaption>U.S. Secretary of State Antony Blinken speaks to reporters about the war between Israel and Hamas and the situation in Gaza as he boards his aircraft to depart Washington on travel to the Middle East and Asia at Joint Base Andrews, Maryland, U.S., November 2, 2023. REUTERS/Jonathan Ernst/Pool翻译:2023 年 11 月 2 日，美国国务卿安东尼·布林肯在美国马里兰州安德鲁斯联合基地登上飞机离开华盛顿前往中东和亚洲，向记者讲述以色列和哈马斯之间的战争以及加沙局势. 路透社/乔纳森·恩斯特/普尔</figcaption></figure>    <figure><img src="https://www.reuters.com/resizer/hbpbD9Sao0h9eCP6qNH3_S2J4Vc=/1920x0/filters:quality(80)/cloudfront-us-east-2.images.arcpublishing.com/reuters/7KIITBBCGFI35DTRN4IWU6Z34M.jpg" alt="South Africa hosts US-Africa trade summit" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"><figcaption>Ambassador Katherine Tai, United States Trade Representative, speaks during the opening of the U.S.-sub-Saharan Africa trade forum to discuss the future of the African Growth and Opportunity Act (AGOA), at the NASREC conference center in Johannesburg, South Africa, November 3, 2023. REUTERS/Siphiwe Sibeko翻译:11 月，美国贸易代表凯瑟琳·戴大使在南非约翰内斯堡 NASREC 会议中心举行的美国撒哈拉以南非洲贸易论坛开幕式上发表讲话，讨论非洲增长与机会法案 (AGOA) 的未来2023 年 3 月。路透社/Siphiwe Sibeko</figcaption></figure>               <p>President Joe Biden's administration wants to work with Congress to improve the United States' flagship trade programme with Africa, not just renew it without changes, U.S. Secretary of State Antony Blinken said on Friday.翻译:美国国务卿安东尼·布林肯周五表示，乔·拜登总统的政府希望与国会合作，改善美国对非洲的旗舰贸易计划，而不仅仅是不做任何修改地续签该计划。</p>   <p>First launched in 2000, the <a href="https://www.reuters.com/world/us-african-growth-opportunity-act-agoa-2023-11-01/">African Growth and Opportunity Act</a> (AGOA) grants exports from qualifying African countries duty-free access to the United States - the world's largest consumer market.翻译:<a href="https://www.reuters.com/world/us-african-growth-opportunity-act-agoa-2023-11-01/">《非洲增长与机会法案》</a> (AGOA) 于 2000 年首次推出，允许符合条件的非洲国家的出口产品免税进入美国这一全球最大的消费市场。</p>   <p>It is due to expire in September 2025, and <a href="https://www.reuters.com/business/retail-consumer/african-apparel-industrys-future-hangs-us-thread-2023-11-01/">discussions</a> are currently under way over what would be its third reauthorisation.翻译:该授权将于 2025 年 9 月到期，目前正在<a href="https://www.reuters.com/business/retail-consumer/african-apparel-industrys-future-hangs-us-thread-2023-11-01/">讨论</a>第三次重新授权。</p>   <p>African countries are pushing for an early <a href="https://www.reuters.com/world/africa-us-trade-programme-needs-least-10-year-extension-au-says-2023-11-02/">10-year extension</a> without changes to reassure businesses and investors.翻译:非洲国家正在推动在不做任何改变的情况下提前<a href="https://www.reuters.com/world/africa-us-trade-programme-needs-least-10-year-extension-au-says-2023-11-02/">延长 10 年</a>，以安抚企业和投资者。</p>   <p>Despite longstanding bipartisan support from U.S. lawmakers, who view AGOA as critical in countering the influence of China in Africa, there are divisions over the need for updates.翻译:尽管美国立法者长期以来一直支持两党，他们认为《非洲增长机会法案》对于对抗中国在非洲的影响至关重要，但对于更新的必要性存在分歧。</p>   <p>A <a href="https://www.scott.senate.gov/imo/media/doc/senator_scott_leads_call_to_renew_agoa_to_combat_chinese_and_russian_influence_in_africa_provide_certainty_for_usbusinesses.pdf" target="_blank">recent push</a> in the U.S. Senate is aiming to pass a quick AGOA renewal. Biden has also said he fully supports the initiative's reauthorisation.翻译:美国参议院<a href="https://www.scott.senate.gov/imo/media/doc/senator_scott_leads_call_to_renew_agoa_to_combat_chinese_and_russian_influence_in_africa_provide_certainty_for_usbusinesses.pdf" target="_blank">最近的一项努力</a>旨在快速通过《非洲增长机会法案》的续签。拜登还表示，他完全支持该倡议的重新授权。</p>   <p>"But we don't just want to extend AGOA, we want to work with the United States Congress to make it even better," Blinken said in a video message to U.S. officials and African trade ministers meeting in Johannesburg to discuss AGOA's future.翻译:布林肯在给在约翰内斯堡开会讨论 AGOA 未来的美国官员和非洲贸易部长的视频信息中表示：“但我们不仅仅想延长 AGOA，我们还希望与美国国会合作，使其变得更好。”</p>    <h 1="">'FORWARD-LOOKING VISION'</h>  <p>Over $10 billion worth of African exports entered the United States duty free last year under the programme. However, the U.S. International Trade Commission earlier this year highlighted major shortcomings.翻译:去年，根据该计划，价值超过 100 亿美元的非洲出口产品免税进入美国。然而，美国国际贸易委员会今年早些时候强调了重大缺陷。</p>   <p>More than 80% of duty-free non-petroleum AGOA exports, for example, have come from just five countries - South Africa, Kenya, Lesotho, Madagascar and Ethiopia - in recent years.翻译:例如，近年来，超过 80% 的免税非石油类 AGOA 出口仅来自五个国家——南非、肯尼亚、莱索托、马达加斯加和埃塞俄比亚。</p>   <p>"We see that there is opportunity to shape a stronger, new, forward-looking vision for U.S.-Africa trade," U.S. Trade Representative Katherine Tai, who is leading the U.S. delegation, told the African ministers.翻译:美国代表团团长、美国贸易代表凯瑟琳·戴对非洲部长们表示：“我们看到有机会为美非贸易塑造更强大、新的、前瞻性的愿景。”</p>   <p>African governments and U.S. industry associations, however, worry that attempts to radically alter AGOA risk bogging the programme's renewal down in a Congress that is already struggling to pass even the most critical legislation.翻译:然而，非洲各国政府和美国行业协会担心，从根本上改变《非洲增长机会法案》的尝试可能会导致该计划的更新陷入困境，而国会已经在努力通过最关键的立法。</p>   <p>"We would like you to look at an extension of AGOA for a sufficiently lengthy period ... to act as an incentive for investors to build factories on the African continent," South African President Cyril Ramaphosa told the forum.翻译:南非总统西里尔·拉马福萨在论坛上表示：“我们希望大家考虑将《非洲增长机会法案》延长足够长的一段时间……以激励投资者在非洲大陆建设工厂。”</p>   <p>African governments are also pushing for more flexibility concerning eligibility criteria and a loosening of what is now an annual review of those criteria.翻译:非洲各国政府也在推动资格标准更加灵活，并放宽目前对这些标准的年度审查。</p>   <p>The Biden administration said on Oct. 30 it intended to <a href="https://www.reuters.com/world/africa/us-end-participation-gabon-niger-uganda-central-african-republic-trade-program-2023-10-30/">end the participation</a> of Gabon, Niger, Uganda and the Central African Republic in AGOA over governance and rights failings.翻译:拜登政府10月30日表示，由于治理和权利缺陷，打算<a href="https://www.reuters.com/world/africa/us-end-participation-gabon-niger-uganda-central-african-republic-trade-program-2023-10-30/">终止加蓬、尼日尔、乌干达和中非共和国参与</a>AGOA。</p>   <p>Harriet Ntabazi, trade minister of Uganda, whose country was suspended over "gross violations" of internationally recognised human rights, said such issues should be separated from trade.翻译:乌干达贸易部长哈里特·恩塔巴齐(Harriet Ntabazi)表示，此类问题应与贸易分开。乌干达因“严重侵犯”国际公认的人权而被停职。</p>   <p>Ugandan government officials have linked their exclusion to an <a href="https://www.reuters.com/world/africa/ugandas-anti-gay-law-causing-wave-rights-abuses-activists-say-2023-09-28/">anti-homosexuality</a> law that was passed by its parliament in May.翻译:乌干达政府官员将他们的排斥与议会五月通过的<a href="https://www.reuters.com/world/africa/ugandas-anti-gay-law-causing-wave-rights-abuses-activists-say-2023-09-28/">反同性恋</a>法联系起来。</p>   <p>"Mistakes are human. If they have been done, reconsider and we go into negotiations. We've never had this chance to sit together and agree. Give us another chance," Ntabazi said.翻译:“人都会犯错误。如果犯了错误，请重新考虑，然后我们进行谈判。我们从来没有机会坐在一起达成一致。再给我们一次机会，”恩塔巴齐说。</p>    <span>Additional reporting by Carien du Plessis;
